<p>Ron Dermer, a close ally of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu who served as Israel’s minister of strategic affairs, resigned from the cabinet in a move reported on Tuesday. Dermer played a visible role in negotiating a ceasefire in the Gaza war and in talks over the return of hostages, and he served previously as Israel’s ambassador to Washington from 2013 to 2021. In a letter released to the media he said he had reached a personal decision to end his ministerial role and pledged to continue working &quot;to secure the future of the Jewish people,&quot; while offering praise for the prime minister and the government’s wartime conduct.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/KSGy0j3zlyHdoq01tWeD87M901zXwLH62WUv81sIkn_IpotK0ipQFOuD4hUc0FuPgHKDdcTSUYZBvIapy6HB4XsfldwyHqfjGPko9NbQvMvO_BumJtGa1YOJX20Vz2UdO3a8y1u6OJ213HSDrzUzc1NeY-tJqsOC1onYyQVrtz8LTSSLNrtuJfzrRSe_bU55zyei_goQupESx_yLF2FbYbesb8ZUxd1ZHp_kFhZoAOI' alt='Ron Dermer, Israel’s minister of strategic affairs, during a visit to the White House, in July.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Media speculation: Israeli outlets ran weeks of reports and speculation about Dermer’s future before the resignation was announced.</li><li>Personal reasons cited: Dermer wrote that he had promised his family he would serve no more than two years and said he had twice extended that commitment with their blessing.</li><li>Extensions explained: He said his first extension was to work on removing Iran’s military nuclear threat in June and the second to negotiate an October ceasefire and secure hostages’ return.</li><li>Washington background: Before his ministerial post, Dermer was Israel’s ambassador to the United States from 2013 until 2021, giving him deep ties in Washington.</li></ul><blockquote>In our darkest hour, the people of Israel had worthy leaders - Ron Dermer</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Ron Dermer: He said he had promised his family he would serve for no more than two years and that he had extended that commitment twice to address Iran and negotiate a ceasefire and hostage returns. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/israeli-minister-strategic-affairs-ron-dermer-resigns'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>Times of Israel (Dermer&#x27;s letter): Dermer praised Prime Minister Netanyahu and wrote that &#x27;in our darkest hour, the people of Israel had worthy leaders,&#x27; saying the government will be remembered for Oct. 7 and its response. (<a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/resigning-as-minister-dermer-says-govt-will-be-remembered-for-both-oct-7-and-its-response/'>The Times of Israel</a>)</li><li>Israeli media: Multiple outlets had reported weeks of speculation about Dermer’s role and future before the resignation was confirmed. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/israeli-minister-of-strategic-affairs-ron-dermer-resigns'>The Straits Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.al-monitor.com/originals/2025/11/israeli-minister-strategic-affairs-ron-dermer-has-resigned-israeli-media-reports'>Israeli Minister of Strategic Affairs Ron Dermer has resigned, Israeli media reports</a> - al-monitor.com</li><li><a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/resigning-as-minister-dermer-says-govt-will-be-remembered-for-both-oct-7-and-its-response/'>Resigning as minister, Dermer says gov’t will be remembered for both Oct. 7 and its response</a> - timesofisrael.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/israeli-minister-of-strategic-affairs-ron-dermer-resigns'>Israel’s Minister of Strategic Affairs Ron Dermer resigns</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/11/world/middleeast/israel-ron-dermer-resigns-netanyahu.html'>Key Netanyahu Minister Steps Down From Israel’s Government</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/israeli-minister-strategic-affairs-ron-dermer-resigns'>Israeli Minister of Strategic Affairs Ron Dermer resigns</a> - newarab.com</li></ul>